{
  "id": "2024-05-15_screen_english",
  "date": "2024-05-15",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "Tap dancing was my specialty",
  "movie": "",
  "duration_sec": 545.35,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2024-05-15_screen_english.mp3",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 14.95,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 14.95,
      "end": 35.26,
      "text": "영화가 즐거워지는 영어 놀이터 스크린 잉글리쉬 타임"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.26,
      "end": 41.14,
      "text": "워렌, 앤토니 홉킨스, 올리비아 콜맨 주연, 플로리안 젤러 감독의"
    },
    {
      "start": 41.14,
      "end": 41.98,
      "text": "The Father"
    },
    {
      "start": 41.98,
      "end": 42.54,
      "text": "입니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 42.54,
      "end": 47.12,
      "text": "와우 오늘도 다정한 목소리로 와주셨습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.12,
      "end": 48.58,
      "text": "I'm here, hello"
    },
    {
      "start": 48.58,
      "end": 50.76,
      "text": "네, 우리 크리스씨 반갑구요"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.76,
      "end": 51.46,
      "text": "What's up?"
    },
    {
      "start": 51.62,
      "end": 53.52,
      "text": "와, 오늘 Happy Teacher's Day"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.52,
      "end": 54.92,
      "text": "Oh, is it Teacher's Day?"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.02,
      "end": 57.14,
      "text": "Yeah, is there a day like this in the US?"
    },
    {
      "start": 57.34,
      "end": 60.14,
      "text": "Wow, well I haven't been in the US in a while"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.14,
      "end": 62.8,
      "text": "but there was a Teacher's Day"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.8,
      "end": 66.52,
      "text": "In May, and I think it's May 6th"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.52,
      "end": 70.06,
      "text": "Right now there's a Teacher's, it's called Teacher's Appreciation Week"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.06,
      "end": 72.8,
      "text": "So the actual day is May 6th"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.8,
      "end": 74.34,
      "text": "선생님들 너무 좋으시겠어요"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.34,
      "end": 75.86,
      "text": "이렇게 생일 주간처럼"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.86,
      "end": 76.44,
      "text": "Sure"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.44,
      "end": 78.26,
      "text": "선생님의 주간이 되겠네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.26,
      "end": 78.82,
      "text": "주간"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.82,
      "end": 79.2,
      "text": "와우"
    },
    {
      "start": 79.2,
      "end": 80.82,
      "text": "하루보다 주간이 길고 좋죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.82,
      "end": 81.62,
      "text": "그럼요"
    },
    {
      "start": 81.62,
      "end": 83.76,
      "text": "네, 선물 많이 받았으면 좋겠고요"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.76,
      "end": 85.48,
      "text": "네, 학생들이 바쁘겠네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.48,
      "end": 87.5,
      "text": "They should appreciate their teachers"
    },
    {
      "start": 87.5,
      "end": 88.22,
      "text": "맞습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.22,
      "end": 91.08,
      "text": "When I was a kid, we didn't always give them presents"
    },
    {
      "start": 91.08,
      "end": 94.84,
      "text": "But, you know, I definitely had wonderful teachers"
    },
    {
      "start": 94.84,
      "end": 99.58,
      "text": "So if I could see them today, I'll give them a big hug and a gift card"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.58,
      "end": 100.9,
      "text": "우와, 진짜요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.16,
      "end": 103.04,
      "text": "Yeah, not all of my teachers"
    },
    {
      "start": 103.04,
      "end": 105.62,
      "text": "Some of my teachers, you know, not my favorite"
    },
    {
      "start": 105.62,
      "end": 108.06,
      "text": "But I had a few very special teachers"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.06,
      "end": 110.78,
      "text": "어떤 선생님들이 기억에 남으시나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 110.78,
      "end": 111.98,
      "text": "Uh, first grade"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.98,
      "end": 113.12,
      "text": "No, second grade"
    },
    {
      "start": 113.12,
      "end": 113.76,
      "text": "Second grade"
    },
    {
      "start": 113.76,
      "end": 114.48,
      "text": "Mrs. Sokol"
    },
    {
      "start": 114.48,
      "end": 116.14,
      "text": "She had the biggest smile"
    },
    {
      "start": 116.14,
      "end": 117.42,
      "text": "She was always smiling"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.42,
      "end": 117.82,
      "text": "네"
    },
    {
      "start": 117.82,
      "end": 119.84,
      "text": "So I don't remember anything she taught me"
    },
    {
      "start": 119.84,
      "end": 120.22,
      "text": "Oh"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.22,
      "end": 122.14,
      "text": "But she made me feel good"
    },
    {
      "start": 122.14,
      "end": 126.08,
      "text": "And I was, you were laughing, huh?"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.28,
      "end": 127.06,
      "text": "아, 빵빵더지 않아요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.14,
      "end": 127.46,
      "text": "아, 네"
    },
    {
      "start": 127.46,
      "end": 129.74,
      "text": "I have no idea what I learned in second grade"
    },
    {
      "start": 129.74,
      "end": 132.2,
      "text": "But just the way someone makes you feel"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.2,
      "end": 132.54,
      "text": "네"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.54,
      "end": 133.94,
      "text": "That's what you remember the most"
    },
    {
      "start": 133.94,
      "end": 134.36,
      "text": "Wow"
    },
    {
      "start": 134.36,
      "end": 135.8,
      "text": "And she encouraged me"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.8,
      "end": 137.2,
      "text": "She gave me confidence"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.2,
      "end": 137.54,
      "text": "네"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.54,
      "end": 139.4,
      "text": "She flattered me with compliments"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.4,
      "end": 140.04,
      "text": "그렇죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.04,
      "end": 141.92,
      "text": "And she just loved me"
    },
    {
      "start": 141.92,
      "end": 143.26,
      "text": "I felt love from her"
    },
    {
      "start": 143.26,
      "end": 148.06,
      "text": "어, 그 선생님의 애정 다 한 푹 담긴 미소만 바라봐도"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.06,
      "end": 150.72,
      "text": "많은 것을 배우셨을 겁니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.72,
      "end": 151.7,
      "text": "그거 더 중요하죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 151.7,
      "end": 152.3,
      "text": "그럼요"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.3,
      "end": 154.3,
      "text": "무슨 지식 중요합니까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 154.96,
      "end": 155.94,
      "text": "감정이 중요하죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 155.94,
      "end": 156.5,
      "text": "아무튼"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.5,
      "end": 157.3,
      "text": "기분 좋게"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.3,
      "end": 160.24,
      "text": "아, 오늘도 이렇게 빵빵 터지게 해주셔서 너무 감사드리네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.24,
      "end": 162.88,
      "text": "조세님은, do you have any memorable teachers?"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.14,
      "end": 163.82,
      "text": "아, of course"
    },
    {
      "start": 163.82,
      "end": 164.68,
      "text": "당연히 있죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 164.68,
      "end": 165.84,
      "text": "Are you thankful?"
    },
    {
      "start": 166.1,
      "end": 166.78,
      "text": "아, 그럼요"
    },
    {
      "start": 166.78,
      "end": 168.56,
      "text": "여전히 연락도 드리고"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.56,
      "end": 168.98,
      "text": "와"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.98,
      "end": 171.24,
      "text": "오늘도 연락을 드려야 되겠네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 171.24,
      "end": 171.62,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 171.62,
      "end": 173.0,
      "text": "말 나온 김에"
    },
    {
      "start": 173.0,
      "end": 175.64,
      "text": "꼭 메시지를 드리겠습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 175.64,
      "end": 176.52,
      "text": "Give him a call"
    },
    {
      "start": 176.52,
      "end": 177.66,
      "text": "or a message"
    },
    {
      "start": 177.66,
      "end": 178.76,
      "text": "어, 두 개 다 할게요"
    },
    {
      "start": 178.76,
      "end": 179.72,
      "text": "Very nice"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.72,
      "end": 181.0,
      "text": "먼저 메시지 보내고"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.0,
      "end": 182.12,
      "text": "그 다음에 전화드리고"
    },
    {
      "start": 182.12,
      "end": 183.88,
      "text": "좋습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.88,
      "end": 184.78,
      "text": "아, 너무 좋아하겠네요"
    },
    {
      "start": 184.78,
      "end": 187.3,
      "text": "네, 그나저나 우리의 그 앤토니가요"
    },
    {
      "start": 187.3,
      "end": 190.96,
      "text": "점점 기억력이 더 안 좋아지는 것 같더라고요"
    },
    {
      "start": 190.96,
      "end": 192.74,
      "text": "Yeah, it's deteriorating"
    },
    {
      "start": 192.74,
      "end": 195.44,
      "text": "It's getting progressively worse and worse"
    },
    {
      "start": 195.44,
      "end": 197.06,
      "text": "오, 너무 안타까워요"
    },
    {
      "start": 197.06,
      "end": 200.22,
      "text": "우리가 이렇게 추억을 가지고 살아가는 게 인간인데"
    },
    {
      "start": 200.22,
      "end": 203.36,
      "text": "이 추억이 점점 희미해지고 있단 말이죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.36,
      "end": 205.08,
      "text": "음, 되게 옛날 추억"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.08,
      "end": 205.74,
      "text": "그러게요"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.74,
      "end": 207.88,
      "text": "I mean, today I don't remember anything"
    },
    {
      "start": 207.88,
      "end": 209.58,
      "text": "but my childhood memories"
    },
    {
      "start": 209.58,
      "end": 211.1,
      "text": "are the ones that are special"
    },
    {
      "start": 211.1,
      "end": 214.12,
      "text": "네, 자, 그럼 오늘 장면도 듣고 오시죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 214.12,
      "end": 215.94,
      "text": "What about you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.0,
      "end": 216.96,
      "text": "What did you do for a living?"
    },
    {
      "start": 217.62,
      "end": 218.5,
      "text": "Oh, I was a dancer"
    },
    {
      "start": 218.5,
      "end": 219.68,
      "text": "Were you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 219.76,
      "end": 220.1,
      "text": "Yes"
    },
    {
      "start": 220.1,
      "end": 220.5,
      "text": "Dad?"
    },
    {
      "start": 220.7,
      "end": 221.02,
      "text": "What?"
    },
    {
      "start": 222.44,
      "end": 223.24,
      "text": "You're an engineer"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.24,
      "end": 225.3,
      "text": "But you know about it"
    },
    {
      "start": 225.3,
      "end": 227.71,
      "text": "Yes, tap dancing was my specialty"
    },
    {
      "start": 227.71,
      "end": 228.53,
      "text": "Really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 228.87,
      "end": 229.79,
      "text": "You seem surprised"
    },
    {
      "start": 229.79,
      "end": 230.97,
      "text": "Yeah, a little bit"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.97,
      "end": 232.65,
      "text": "Why, don't you believe me?"
    },
    {
      "start": 232.79,
      "end": 234.35,
      "text": "Oh, you find that difficult to imagine?"
    },
    {
      "start": 234.35,
      "end": 238.63,
      "text": "오, 근데 탭댄스가 이게 쉽지가 않아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.63,
      "end": 239.79,
      "text": "Have you tried it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 239.93,
      "end": 240.53,
      "text": "아니요"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.53,
      "end": 242.41,
      "text": "그럼 어떻게 알아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 242.41,
      "end": 245.59,
      "text": "I just saw some people tap dancing"
    },
    {
      "start": 245.59,
      "end": 246.67,
      "text": "And you've seen tap dancers"
    },
    {
      "start": 246.67,
      "end": 247.79,
      "text": "Yeah, on the stage"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.79,
      "end": 248.05,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.05,
      "end": 249.39,
      "text": "오, 근데 그거 진짜"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.39,
      "end": 251.87,
      "text": "어, 발을 어떻게 움직이길래 저런 소리가 나지?"
    },
    {
      "start": 251.97,
      "end": 253.73,
      "text": "They're like drummers with their feet"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.73,
      "end": 254.15,
      "text": "Right"
    },
    {
      "start": 254.15,
      "end": 255.61,
      "text": "They drum with their legs and feet"
    },
    {
      "start": 255.61,
      "end": 255.97,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 255.97,
      "end": 256.59,
      "text": "It's incredible"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.59,
      "end": 256.99,
      "text": "맞아요"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.99,
      "end": 258.85,
      "text": "발로 무슨 드럼을 치는 것 같이"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.85,
      "end": 260.91,
      "text": "그런 현란한 스킬을 보여준단 말이죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 260.91,
      "end": 261.73,
      "text": "Perfect rhythm"
    },
    {
      "start": 261.73,
      "end": 263.49,
      "text": "네, 근데 지금 앤튼이가"
    },
    {
      "start": 263.49,
      "end": 264.85,
      "text": "그 caregiver한테"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.85,
      "end": 265.97,
      "text": "He's lying"
    },
    {
      "start": 265.97,
      "end": 267.73,
      "text": "That he was a tap dancer"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.73,
      "end": 268.57,
      "text": "Liar!"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.71,
      "end": 270.55,
      "text": "He said he was a tap dancer"
    },
    {
      "start": 270.55,
      "end": 273.25,
      "text": "딱 봐도 지금 tap dancing을 못하더라고요"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.25,
      "end": 276.59,
      "text": "I, yeah, I don't think he's ever tap danced in his life"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.59,
      "end": 277.17,
      "text": "그러니까요"
    },
    {
      "start": 277.17,
      "end": 277.81,
      "text": "Like us"
    },
    {
      "start": 277.81,
      "end": 279.95,
      "text": "He was actually an engineer"
    },
    {
      "start": 279.95,
      "end": 280.41,
      "text": "그죠"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.41,
      "end": 282.95,
      "text": "His whole career was an engineering"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.95,
      "end": 283.47,
      "text": "Yeah"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.47,
      "end": 285.03,
      "text": "But I think, what?"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.11,
      "end": 285.77,
      "text": "He likes her?"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.97,
      "end": 287.19,
      "text": "He wanted to impress her?"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.37,
      "end": 290.61,
      "text": "아마 아무래도 로라가 너무 마음에 들어가지고"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.61,
      "end": 292.91,
      "text": "자꾸만 과장을 하고 싶었나 봐요"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.91,
      "end": 295.29,
      "text": "아, 인지니어를 더 좋아할 수도 있는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 295.29,
      "end": 296.19,
      "text": "그러게요"
    },
    {
      "start": 296.19,
      "end": 301.59,
      "text": "뭐, 엔지니어라고 앤이 옆에서 정정을 해주지 않았다고 하더라도"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.59,
      "end": 305.45,
      "text": "그게 거짓말이라는 것을 우리도 충분히 느낄 수 있을 정도였으니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.45,
      "end": 306.47,
      "text": "아, 뼈저리게"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.47,
      "end": 307.61,
      "text": "뻥"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.61,
      "end": 309.83,
      "text": "네, 뼈저리게 뻥 이었습니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.83,
      "end": 312.81,
      "text": "그럼 주요 표현부터 점검을 해볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 312.81,
      "end": 314.85,
      "text": "What did you do for a living?"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.27,
      "end": 316.79,
